This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques for automated classification of chief complaints from patient-generated text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and ML techniques for processing and understanding human language. The paper also evaluates several approaches to chief complaint classification, which involves fine-tuning transformer models, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for classifying chief complaints, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves the use of BERT models, which are a type of deep learning model, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with healthcare data, which could place it in cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it involves the intersection of computing and healthcare.
